The Patriotic Alliance this week attempted to shut down illegal foreign-owned shops in Eldorado Park. The party has taken a controversial stance on undocumented immigrants, and its radical views gained traction during the local government elections. The assault on foreign-owned shops however has been received with mixed feelings in the Johannesburg south community where the party holds sway. eNCA’s Lee McCabe has the details.#DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The Patriotic Alliance attempted to shut down illegal foreign-owned shops in Eldorado Park. The party has taken a controversial stance on undocumented immigrants, and its radical views gained traction during the local government elections. The assault on foreign-owned shops however has been received with mixed feelings in the Johannesburg south community where the party holds sway. A hard-line adopted in a community riddled with socio-economic problems. READ: 2021 Municipal Elections | Patriotic Alliance emerges as kingmaker This foreign-owned spaza shop in Eldorado Park was the first target of the Patriotic Alliance, which won the ward in a landslide. Eldorado Park has a high unemployment rate and many residents buy from these shops because they are more affordable. The Patriotic Alliance vowed to continue its operation. Watch the video above for more details on this story.